complications. The goal is to create a dynamic class that makes reflection calls without introducing external dependencies. However, there’s a concern about whether this approach is permissible and if it truly represents the ICU4J library. I might need to consider adding a real dependency instead to maintain integrity and coverage. Also, I should check style guidelines!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering testing tools**\\n\\nI need to use the @Test annotation from Jupiter, which seems straightforward. Also, I could incorporate AssertJ for my assertions—assertThat will be useful here. It's crucial to ensure that there's no \\\"$\\\" present in the assertions or test cases to avoid issues. I want to keep everything clean and efficient, so I’ll double-check that I'm implementing these correctly. It’s all about making sure the tests are accurate and consistent!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering API and dependencies**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the public API of H2, which seems good. I don't need to worry about NativeImageSupport because there's no open-ended dynamic class loading here. The ICU4J class is loaded by name, known at image build, and since it's included as a dependency, I'm not dealing with reflection in a dynamic sense. I also need to ensure the build.gradle tab matches existing tabs and add the necessary dependency.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_boNjI0OPy09j3L14euzt3iaW|fc_021c0e0f3a330fe30169f9a0b19d10819db46065f32cf296c5", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.1.210/src/test/java/h2/CompareModeIcu4JTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage h2;\n\nimport org.h2.value.CompareMode;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport java.text.Collator;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class CompareModeIcu4JTest {\n    @Test\n    void usesIcu4jCollatorForLanguageName() {\n        CompareMode mode = CompareMode.getInstance(CompareMode.ICU4J + \"en\", Collator.TERTIARY);\n\n        assertThat(mode.compareString(\"H2\", \"H2\", false)).isZero();\n        assertThat(mode.compareString(\"H2\", \"h2\", true)).isZero();\n        assertThat(mode.equalsChars(\"A\", 0, \"a\", 0, true)).isTrue();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void usesIcu4jCollatorForLanguageAndCountryName() {\n        CompareMode mode = CompareMode.getInstance(CompareMode.ICU4J + \"en_US\", Collator.SECONDARY);\n\n        assertThat(mode.compareString(\"database\", \"database\", false)).isZero();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void resolvesHyphenatedIcu4jLocaleFromAvailableLocales() {\n        CompareMode mode = CompareMode.getInstance(CompareMode.ICU4J + \"en-US\", Collator.PRIMARY);\n\n        assertThat(mode.compareString(\"coverage\", \"coverage\", false)).isZero();\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 758, "output": 1363, "cacheRead": 24064, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 26185, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777967267178, "responseId": "resp_021c0e0f3a330fe30169f9a0a3a27c819d995a84e41e3cd3a1"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_boNjI0OPy09j3L14euzt3iaW|fc_021c0e0f3a330fe30169f9a0b19d10819db46065f32cf296c5", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1289 bytes to tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.1.210/src/test/java/h2/CompareModeIcu4JTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777967283513}]}
